Retro gaming company Hyperkin has unveiled its new X91 Xbox One controller. The X91 sports a unique design inspired by classic devices such as the Sega Genesis controller. The controller is compatible with the Xbox One and Windows 10, and is smaller than the standard Xbox One controller. The X91 is available for pre-order on Amazon for $30 and will be available from 21 February. The device is available in Black, Red, and White.   